Hospital:
 Rapides Regional Medical Center

Location: Alexandria, Louisiana

Address: 211
 Fourth Street, Alexandria, LA 71301

Unit Name: 
3A Cardiovascular

Building: 3rd Floor, South Tower

Cost Center: 63073

General Information

Unit Specifics: 
Number of Beds :
 20Patient Ratios :
 5 or 6 : 1Unit staffing description: 3A is a total of 20 beds surrounding one nursing station.
 There is a secretary on duty from 7am to 10 pm daily and from 7am to 7pm on the weekends, census permitting.
 PCTs are available all three shifts and ratio fluctuates with census and shifts. There is no free charge nurse on 3a, however, there is a tremendous amount of teamwork on this floor where staff are very helpful to one another. This floor is known for having excellent patient satisfaction scores. Type of equipment: Each patient is monitored on telemetry boxes, with the monitor in the nurse s station to view all patients on the unit.
 Dynamaps with neurons that upload vital signs directly to Meditech.
 Glucometers also upload results directly to Meditech.
 Use of iMobile phones and technology by all staff in the hospital.
 iPhones are tied into call system for direct patient access to available staff.Documentation system:
 Meditech using EBCD (Evidence Based Clinical Documentation)Scheduling requirements:
 All nursing shift are twelve hours from 7 to 7; every other weekend.
 Holiday requirements.Floating policy:
 Nursing staff will float to other Medical-Surgical Units in the hospital as needed with primary focus on pulling to similar units.
 Patient Experience requirements:
 Hourly rounding, bedside hand-off reporting, completion of  My Care Board  during hand-off report; use of AIDET with a focus on compassionate connected care.
Hospital Specifics-
Pathways to Excellence CertifiedWorking toward Magnet statusCertified Stroke CenterCertified Chest Pain CenterLevel II Trauma Center
Hiring profile

Requested Skill Set:
 Femoral arterial sheath removal; PICC line removal; Radial band care and removal; post heart cath/PCI care; temporary and permanent pacemaker care; knowledge of core measure requirements. In addition, must be familiar with management of chest tubes. 




Must have: 
 Positive attitude, flexibility, teamwork, desire for excellence, self-motivated, good communication and people skills, ability to work in a diverse environment







Advanced skills needed:
 Telemetry rhythm interpretation







Procedures performed on unit: 
Post Cardiac catheterization/PCI; Post pacemaker care; Cardioversions; PICC line placement







Certifications Required:
 ACLS, BLS







